Group 3


1.Availability for meeting expectations. 
1R) We will decide on a weekly basis. For next week we expect to meet on Monday at 2pm. 
2.Response time to communication expectations
2R) We will communicate with Microsoft Teams.
3.Definition of done: when is a task complete? (hint: "I'm done with that but I didn't check it in to github" is not done.). 
3R) A task is done when the task is commited and merged to the main github project. 
4.Scrum meeting format/frequency and distribution of documentation tasks (meeting minutes, updating task board)
4R) In Scrum we do daily 15 minutes stand ups and update the task board as we progress with the task. 
5.Procedure for adopting policies (e.g. code style, code check-in steps, documentation updates)
  a.if you adopt such a policy during the initial meeting, put it here
5R) Comments are expected to be explicit and informative for the rest of the group. That involves good method definition for instance. We are also to meet set deadlines. 
6.Procedure for handling a member who is not meeting expectations
  a.must include at least 3 actions before involving the instructor
6R) For the first time, a kind remark will be sufficient and another person will complete the task. For the second time, one member will contact him over a teams call. For the third time, we will discuss the issue as a group.
7.Signatures: each member must sign their name by typing their name at the bottom of the document.
